modules.description: Provides functions to create inline elements like text, emphasis, links, and images, as well as block elements such as paragraphs, lists, blockquotes, and code blocks. Works with inline and block-level AST structures, including attributes as key-value lists. Constructs formatted documents by combining elements like emphasized text within a paragraph or nested lists with custom spacing.

Processes Markdown documents by parsing them into an abstract syntax tree, transforming nodes, and rendering output in HTML or other formats. Operates on structured data including blocks, inline elements, and document hierarchies. Enables tasks such as extracting headers for table of contents generation or modifying code blocks for syntax highlighting.

Encapsulates document structure through inline and block elements, supporting text formatting, links, lists, and code blocks with attribute handling. Key types include inline and block AST nodes, with operations for building and combining elements. Users can construct complex documents, such as a paragraph containing emphasized text or a nested list with custom spacing. Provides precise control over document composition through structured element creation and manipulation.
